section.section:
Each review board consists of 11 members appointed:
by the county commissioners;
in Baltimore City, by the Mayor with the advice and consent of the City Council;
in any county that has a county executive, by the county executive with the advice and consent of the county council; or
if 2 or more counties have agreed to establish a multicounty review board, jointly by the appropriate officials of the counties served by the board.

Of the 11 members:
1 shall be a professional representative of a local department;
in counties other than St. Mary's County, 2 shall be physicians, including 1 psychiatrist from a local health department that employs psychiatrists; and
in St. Mary's County, 1 shall be a physician other than a psychiatrist and 1 shall be a psychiatrist or psychologist from the local health department;
1 shall be a representative of a local commission on aging;
1 shall be a professional representative of a local nonprofit social service organization;
1 shall be a lawyer;
2 shall be lay individuals;
1 shall be a public health nurse;
1 shall be a professional in the field of disabilities; and
1 shall be a person with a physical disability.
